            <scopecontent id="aspace_eadc4ae8d107a267d320ca8b8fadf64e">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The papers consist of materials created and accumulated by Silverman while serving as director of the Workers' Health Bureau of America and executive-secretary of the People's National Health Committee (PNHC). The files relating to the PNHC comprise the bulk of the collection. The files are comprised of correspondence, reports, and publications. A significant portion of the files consists of materials relating to the Wagner Health Bill, for which the PNHC was created to support. Files related to the bill include correspondence, drafts of the bill, recommendations for amendments, and research material. Another significant portion of the files relates to the <title render="italic">
                     <part>People's Health Bulletin</part>
                  </title>. The <title render="italic">
                     <part>Bulletin</part>
                  </title> files consist primarily of materials for inclusion submitted by various people involved in workers' health rights.</p>
               <p>Files documenting Silverman's activities as director and education secretary of the Workers' Health Bureau of America include correspondence, publications, and reports. The correspondence consists primarily of correspondence between Silverman and Grace Burnham and Charlotte Todes, executive secretary and organizing secretary of the Workers' Health Bureau respectively. One file of correspondence regarding a study of women in industry is listed at the end of the correspondence. The administrative reports comprise another pertinent portion of the files. The reports document the activities, goals and dissolution of the Workers' Health Bureau of America.</p>
            </scopecontent>
